default&#xa0;
defaultConclusiondefault&#xa0;
defaultAntimicrobial resistance is one of the biggest public health threats.  
defaultA group of experts in antibiotic resistance and healthcare associated infection 
defaultis
default defaultcalling for changes to establish an environment whereby infection specialists can make the best prescribing decisions for patients.  Diverse (but appropriate) antibiotic prescribing can reduce the selection pressure for resistance and can improve outcomes for current and future patients.
